-- Oil Trading Deals May Come Under New Disclosure Rules, FT Says
-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 2012-04-23T05:17:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/oil-trading-deals-may-come-under-new-disclosure-rules-ft-says.html
Oil-trading companies may come
under new disclosure rules being discussed by the Extractive
Industries Transparency Initiative, the Financial Times reported
today, citing officials involved with the Initiative.  The industry-backed group aimed at improving transparency
in the natural-resources sector is in early talks to extend its
disclosure rules to include deals between national  oil companies 
and traders, the FT said.  The rules may have implications for companies including
Vitol Group, Trafigura AG and Mercuria Energy Trading SA, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ann Koh in Singapore at 
